Contributing to [PROJECT]
=========================

*Legal:* By contributing to [PROJECT], you agree to license your patch under
         the [PROJECT] Public Source License, which is available in the
         COPYRIGHT file.  You also agree with our CODE_OF_CONDUCT.

         You also agree to the Developer Certificate of Origin, available in
         the DCO file.

Test your changes before submitting them, ensure your code style is consistent
with the rest of the codebase.

Before writing any change, open an issue to discuss the change.


Creating a commit
-----------------

Sign-off every commits to show that you agree with the Developer Certificate of
Origin, present in the DCO file.

This can be achieved by adding the

    Signed-off-by: ...

In your commit message body.
